\par\par \uc2 FEATURES\par \b \uc2 GOVT RELYING ON VACCINE DRIVE,  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMIC STIMULUS \highlight\uc2  TO SCRIPT RECOVERY\b0\par\par\uc2 1,044 \uc2 words\par \uc2 2 March 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Yuni Arisandy Sinaga\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Indonesia has rolled out several measures to stimulate \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, both on the demand and supply side. The pace of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity, however, has not met expectations.\par \par \uc2 This week marks the beginning of efforts to fortify and test various measures undertaken by the government to stimulate \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery.\par \par \uc2 From Monday (March 1, 2021), the government has exempted current value-added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and luxury \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  (PPnBM) for 21 types of new cars.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  -- \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) -- \uc2 has also relaxed the loan to value (LTV) ratio for motor vehicles and housing loans for the period from March to December, 2021.\par \par \uc2 To encourage home purchases, the Ministry of Finance has slashed value added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  (VAT) by 50-100 percent for homes with a value of up to Rp5 billion and purchased until August 31, 2021.\par \par \uc2 Considering some recovery efforts conducted in the last decade, the automotive industry, which is included in the manufacturing sub-sector, has indeed become one of the sectors driving \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity.\par \par \uc2 The manufacturing sector contributes 19.8 percent to Indonesia"s gross domestic product (GDP), and also accounts for a large number of jobs.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the property sector contributes 13.6 percent to the GDP, with a broad \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity chain covering 174 industries, such as cement, steel, paint, and furniture.\par \par \uc2 Therefore, the government is relying on the two industrial sectors to provide multiple \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  benefits to society and is seeking to restore production activities to create more jobs.\par \par \uc2 To stoke \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity, the government has not only relaxed its \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but also the monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . For instance, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has lowered its reference interest rate -- through the BI-7 Day Reverse Repo Rate (BI7DRR) -- to 3.5 percent, the lowest level since it was first introduced in April, 2016.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has continued to reduce the reference interest rate in order to lower rates in the money market, banking and capital markets to boost financing for production and consumption.\par \par \uc2 Those \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  relaxations are expected to revive some \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities that stagnated in 2020. Last year"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance, nevertheless, has highlighted the importance of efforts to restore \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  health to support \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery.\par \par \uc2 In keeping with the Keynesian macroeconomic theory that suggests \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  output is strongly influenced by aggregate demand, consumption should be created to drive the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  cycle.\par \par \uc2 In the midst of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  due to the pandemic, however, \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  consumption has been greatly influenced by expectations and purchasing power. Hence, if the handling of the pandemic improves, consumption will most likely increase.\par \par \uc2 But, if the handling of the pandemic worsens, consumption will be restricted, and that will, in turn, affect the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  cycle.\par \par \uc2 Shot in the arm\par \par \uc2 President \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2  (Jokowi) has said that the COVID-19 vaccination program is going to be a game changer for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 He has expressed the belief that vaccination will be a key determinant of how quickly people and the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  return to normal.\par \par \uc2 The President, therefore, has ordered that COVID-19 vaccination be carried out as effectively as possible to cover some 181.5 million targeted recipients within one year, or sooner than the Ministry of Health"s plan of 15 months, to achieve herd immunity.\par \par \uc2 "Vaccination is a very crucial key to enable people to go back to normal work, our children can study in school again, and the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  can immediately revive," he remarked.\par \par \uc2 After vaccinating some 1.5 million healthcare workers in the first phase of the national vaccination program, the government inoculated some market traders and service sector actors as part of the second phase of the program in February, 2021.\par \par \uc2 The second phase, which targeted about 17.4 million recipients, was aimed at stemming COVID-19 transmission in markets, shopping centers, hotels, restaurants, and tourist destinations so that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities in those sectors could recover quickly.\par \par \uc2 The government launched the second phase of the vaccination program on February 17, 2021, focusing on traders at the Tanah Abang wholesale market in Central Jakarta, which was visited by President Widodo.\par \par \uc2 The President also witnessed mass vaccinations at Beringharjo Market in Yogyakarta on Monday (March 1, 2021). The vaccination of market traders is expected to be carried out in all provinces in Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 The government will roll out the third phase of mass vaccinations in March this year, which will target some 63.9 million people living in vulnerable areas. The fourth wave of vaccinations will be carried out in April this year, with about 77.2 million vaccine recipients identified based on clusters.\par \par \uc2 Mutual cooperation\par \par \uc2 To achieve herd immunity quickly, the government has also initiated mutual cooperation with the private sector, allowing businesses to carry out independent vaccinations for their employees.\par \par \uc2 By carrying out independent vaccinations instead of waiting for the government vaccination program, business entities could restart operations more quickly.\par \par \uc2 While the national vaccination program is being funded by the government, independent vaccinations for employees and their families are being funded by corporations, businesses, and other legal entities.\par \par \uc2 The government has assured that independent vaccination programs will not interfere with the ongoing government program. Mutual cooperation vaccinations will only be administered through companies, so they cannot be conducted individually.\par \par \uc2 "Independent vaccination will not interfere with the main vaccination initiative run by the government. All citizens have the right to get vaccines provided by the government," said Siti Nadia Tarmizi, Health Ministry spokesperson for the COVID-19 vaccination program.\par \par \uc2 Apart from vaccinations, the government is also continuing to step up contact tracing, mass testing, and treatment of COVID-19 patients.\par \par \uc2 To support the government"s efforts, the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been urged to remain disciplined in implementing health protocols, such as wearing masks, maintaining distance in \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  places, and washing hands with soap.\par \par \uc2 Ensuring \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  discipline to prevent the further spread of the coronavirus as well as making the vaccination program a success is expected to promote \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, though the results may not show instantly.\par \par \uc2 Nevertheless, if vaccination is successful and is accompanied by the successful containment of the coronavirus, the government will have a chance to script an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  revival for Indonesia in 2021.\par \par \uc2 (T.Y012/A/R013/R013) 02-03-2021 22:59:06\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020210302eh32001gt\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
