\par\par \uc2 INTERNATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 APEC\uc2  OFFICIALS ACCELERATE REGIONAL RESPONSE TO COVID-19, BOOST RECOVERY\b0\par\par\uc2 792 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 March 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Yuni Arisandy Sinaga\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Senior officials from 21 \uc2 APEC\uc2  member economies are convening virtually to speed up regional response to the protracted impacts of COVID-19 in order to drive the recovery process.\par \par \uc2 The two-day Senior Officials\u8217\'20\'19 Meeting comes in close heels to a comprehensive discussion on how \uc2 APEC\uc2  will carry forward the commitments made by leaders in 2020 and the development of a 20-year implementation plan by taking into account the challenges and risks posed by the pandemic, according to a written statement issued by the APEC Secretariat and received here on Friday.\par \par \uc2 "We are facing quite a serious challenge this year, driven in part by the health catastrophe that we all face across our region. However, serious \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  challenges now also confront our economies as we look to find a way through this crisis," Vangelis Vitalis, chair of the APEC 2021 Senior Officials, affirmed.\par \par \uc2 In the wake of wider risk of inequality and rising protectionism against a backdrop of looming \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Vitalis highlighted the significance of capturing and featuring all the challenges, as senior officials deliberate on \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  measures and make concerted regional efforts to drive recovery.\par \par \uc2 "There is rising protectionism across the world, which challenges us all to re-think the fundamentals of regional \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  integration. On top of that, the social licence for trade \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  integration is increasingly under strain, as we witness the unequal impact of COVID-19 on women, small businesses, and indigenous people," Vitalis stressed.\par \par \uc2 "As a region, we need to work together to ensure \uc2 APEC\uc2  effectively responds, not just to the immediate crisis but also to the longer-term need to build a sustainable and resilient regional \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  that benefits everyone," he added.\par \par \uc2 During the dialog, \uc2 APEC\uc2  senior officials will seek to realize the need for \uc2 APEC\uc2  to become more sustainable and inclusive for all people, including for women and indigenous people. The focus will be to support their full participation in the region\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , so it can help to drive new thinking and unlock novel ways to address the global pandemic.\par \par \uc2 Officials will also hold discussions on measures to respond to the pandemic through \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and trade policies that strengthen the recovery year. This comprises policies that encourage openness and connectivity as well as lessen friction at the border, with the objective of reducing barriers and making it easier for companies to trade throughout the \uc2 APEC\uc2  region, especially on COVID-19 essential goods.\par \par \uc2 Advancing digital inclusion, infrastructure, and green technology will also be a key focus for \uc2 APEC\uc2  this year. This encompasses promoting digitally-enabled business and trade, striving for regulatory coherence, and resolving issues pertaining to data and digital trade tools.\par \par \uc2 "\uc2 APEC\uc2 , as a regional forum, needs to seize the moment and rise to the occasion by putting together a concrete response that will benefit all," APEC Secretariat\u8217\'20\'19s Executive Director, Rebecca Sta Maria, noted.\par \par \uc2 "We want to see the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  that continues to make trade and investment across markets easier, cheaper, faster, and more sustainable to avoid undermining the significant progress that has been achieved in the region in these areas," Sta Maria remarked.\par \par \uc2 Vitalis concurred by highlighting the importance of \uc2 APEC\uc2  economies working in unison to end \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  on fossil fuels and reducing tariffs on environmental goods and exploring similar work in services.\par \par \uc2 "\uc2 APEC\uc2  needs to show leadership in this area, as is expected from the world\u8217\'20\'19s most dynamic regional \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he remarked.\par \par \uc2 "The trade \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  should be inclusive, beneficial for all, and be an enabler of solutions to some of the most pressing sustainability issues we all face. Identifying environmental goods and services and addressing barriers to their uptake, for instance, can contribute to our collective climate change mitigation efforts," he explained.\par \par \uc2 This year will hold significance for \uc2 APEC\uc2  and New Zealand. With the APEC Putrajaya Vision 2040 agreed upon by leaders last year, member economies are mandated to formulate a detailed plan of action to realize the new vision that will expand on the three \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  drivers of growth: trade and investment; innovation and digitalization; and strong, balanced, secure, sustainable and inclusive growth.\par \par \uc2 "The key is for \uc2 APEC\uc2  to not only be responsive to the immediate crisis but also relevant to the challenges we are all going to confront over the next 20 years," Vitalis expounded.\par \par \uc2 "We are looking to work together with all \uc2 APEC\uc2  member economies to develop this implementation plan in the spirit of what the Putrajaya Vision talks about in terms of equal partnership. Large or small, we were all equal in this important process," he stated.\par \par \uc2 Sumber: Reuters\par \par \uc2 EDITED BY INE\par \par \uc2 (T.Y012/B/H-SHT/H-SHT) 12-03-2021 17:04:00\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020210312eh3c000dx\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
