\par\par \b \uc2 BI holds rate at record low of 3.5 percent to shield rupiah\b0\par\par\uc2 Norman Harsono , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 555 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 March 2021\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 5\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2021 The Jakarta Post \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) \uc2 has decided to maintain its benchmark interest rate at 3.5 percent, the lowest rate since the seven-day reverse repo rate (7DRRR) was introduced in 2016, to protect the rupiah exchange rate amid market \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Following a two-day \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  meeting, the bank has also decided to maintain its deposit facility rate at 2.75 percent and its lending facility rate at 4.25 percent.\par \par \uc2 "This decision aligns with the need to ensure the stability of the rupiah exchange rate from rising global market \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the midst of expected low inflation," BI Governor \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  told a virtual press conference on Thursday.\par \par \uc2 BI recorded rupiah depreciation of 2.62 percent year-to-date (ytd) as global investors dumped emerging market assets on the back of a rebound in United States Treasury yields, driven by the US' positive domestic growth outlook after President \uc2 Joe Biden\uc2  signed a US$1.9 trillion recovery \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  on March 11.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  is expected to accelerate recovery for both the US and the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but it has triggered capital outflows from emerging markets, including Indonesia, putting pressure on these currencies against the US dollar.\par \par \uc2 BI does not expect the \uc2 US Federal Reserve\uc2  to tighten its monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  this year, and projects that the rupiah will stabilize in the near term.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  also cited its low inflation expectation of between 1 and 3 percent this year as another factor that enabled it to maintain the current rates. It added that it had coordinated closely with other stakeholders to maintain price stability.\par \par \uc2 "Going forward, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  is committed to maintaining price stability and strengthening \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  coordination with the government, whether the central or regional administrations," said Perry.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, Statistics Indonesia (BPS) data show that annual inflation dropped to 1.38 percent in February from 1.55 percent in January. The figure was also lower than the government's projected inflation rate of 3 percent for this year, as well as the pre-pandemic rate of 2.98 percent in February 2020.\par \par \uc2 BI had injected Rp 50.29 trillion ($3.48 billion) into local banks to March 16 in an effort to maintain liquidity, as many borrowers are continuing to struggle with loan repayments. It had also injected Rp 65.03 trillion into state coffers by Tuesday through purchases of sovereign debt papers (SBN) to help finance the government's National \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Recovery (PEN) \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  package.\par \par \uc2 The prolonged COVID-19 pandemic has spurred government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  and sapped \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue. The government has allocated Rp 699.43 trillion to the 2021 PEN fund, up 20.6 percent from the actualized 2020 PEN \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  as it doubles down on its vaccine program.\par \par \uc2 Mandiri economist Faisal Rachman stated in a research note on March 18 that he expected BI to maintain its benchmark interest rate in 2021 while continuing with its quantitative easing and macroprudential policies to accelerate recovery.\par \par \uc2 "The low \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  rate is indeed needed for some time, particularly for the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which is forecast to see a gradual recovery. Yet an attractive interest rate differential needs to be maintained to attract capital inflows in contrast to BI's capacity to enact further \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  easing," he noted.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020210321eh3l00003\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
