\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 PRESIDENT STRESSES NO RICE IMPORTS HAVE ENTERED INDONESIA SO FAR\b0\par\par\uc2 342 \uc2 words\par \uc2 27 March 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Indonesian President \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2  has assured farmers that Indonesia will not import rice, at least until June, 2021.\par \par \uc2 "I assure that until June, 2021, no imported rice will enter our country," the President said in a video uploaded through the \uc2 Youtube\uc2  channel of the Presidential Secretariat on Friday.\par \par \uc2 Several parties including secretary general of the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDIP), Hasto Kristiyanto, had objected to the government"s plan to import 1 million tons of rice.\par \par \uc2 Hasto had argued that the rice import would only benefit foreign farmers.\par \par \uc2 "We know that almost in the past three years we have not imported rice,\u8221\'20\'1D the President said.\par \par \uc2 He admitted that there have been agreements with Thailand and Vietnam for the import of rice.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CIt will merely serve as standby stock on account of the pandemic, which is full of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . I stress once again the rice has not entered (Indonesia),\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par \uc2 He also assured that the \uc2 National Logistics Agency\uc2  (Bulog) will absorb farmer"s rice. He said he has instructed Finance Minister \uc2 Sri Mulyani Indrawati\uc2  to help provide \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  funds for the purchase of rice from farmers.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CI know that we are entering the harvest time and the price of farmer"s rice is lower than expected. Therefore, I call for (an immediate halt to) the debate on the import of rice, which can cause the price of farmer"s rice to fall or plummet,\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par \uc2 Earlier, Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs Airlangga Hartarto had hinted that the import of 1 million tons of rice in 2021 was under discussion. Of the total, 500 thousand tons were to be earmarked for the government"s rice \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  and 500 thousand tons to meet Bulog"s needs.\par \par \uc2 Rice stocks need to be maintained since the government requires large quantities of rice for social assistance during \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity restrictions (PPKM), he said. (INE)\par \par \uc2 EDITED BY INE\par \par \uc2 (T.H-SHT/A/H-FDH/H-FDH) 27-03-2021 09:49:27\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020210327eh3r00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
