\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 BANK INDONESIA \highlight\uc2  RAISES GLOBAL  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMIC \highlight\uc2  GROWTH FORECAST TO 5.7 PERCENT\b0\par\par\uc2 457 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 April 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Azis Kurmala\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has revised its growth forecast for the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in 2021 to 5.7 percent, or surpassing the earlier projected 5.1 percent.\par \par \uc2 Governor of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  stated that the forecast for the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to grow 5.7 percent this year will be driven by \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  improvements in the United States (US) and China that are occurring at a swifter pace than other nations.\par \par \uc2 "The global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is forecast to grow at a higher rate than earlier estimated, with the global recovery process becoming increasingly uneven between countries," he remarked at a virtual press conference in Jakarta on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 According to Warjiyo, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in the United States is expected to be stronger in tandem with the vaccination process that is running smoothly and the addition of a larger \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in China that is higher is supported by improving domestic and global demand.\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, stronger global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery is confirmed by the development of several early indicators in March 2021, such as the Purchasing Managers" Index (PMI), consumer confidence, and increasing retail sales in several nations.\par \par \uc2 The governor believes that the volume of trade and global commodity prices also continued to rise, thereby supporting an improvement in the export performance of higher developing nations, including Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 On the other hand, Warjiyo gauged that financial market \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the volatility of US treasury yields is still ongoing in line with improving \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in the United States and market perceptions of the direction of the Fed"s \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The governor explained that this development had an impact on lower capital inflows to most developing nations and impacted the currency pressure in these countries, including Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 Warjiyo noted that the rupiah exchange rate, as of April 19, 2021, depreciated by 1.16 percent, on an average, and 0.15 percent point-to-point as compared to the level at March-end of 2021.\par \par \uc2 This development occurred in line with the ongoing financial market \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  that restrained the inflows of foreign portfolio investment into the domestic financial market.\par \par \uc2 In the wake of this development, the rupiah, until April 19, 2021, recorded a depreciation of some 3.42 percent (ytd) as compared to the level at the end of 2020, or relatively lower than other developing nations, including Brazil, Turkey, and Thailand.\par \par \uc2 "BI continues to strengthen the rupiah exchange rate stabilization \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in accordance with its fundamentals and the operation of market mechanisms through the effectiveness of monetary operations and the availability of liquidity in the market," he stated.\par \par \uc2 EDITED BY INE\par \par \uc2 (T.A063/A/H-SHT/H-SHT) 20-04-2021 18:55:47\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020210420eh4k000rt\par }\page {\par\fs20\uc2 Business\par \b \uc2 Banks Need to Step Up as BI Runs Out Options to Spur Recovery\b0\par\par\uc2 652 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 April 2021\par \uc2 The Jakarta Globe\par \uc2 JGLOBE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. PT Jakarta Globe Media. \par \par \uc2 Jakarta. \uc2 Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's latest decision to keep its benchmark interest rate may indicate that it has no further room to lower its interest rate this year as higher global yields growing higher and weaker rupiah limit its options, shifting the crux to the local banks lower to their lending \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to support the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , kept the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  rate on hold at 3.5 percent for the second straight month in line with the consensus on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2 , the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's governor, said the "the decision is consistent with the need to maintain rupiah exchange rate stability amidst persistently elevated global financial market \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  despite projected low inflation."\par \par \uc2 For \uc2 Joseph Incalcaterra\uc2 , an economist at HSBC, and Maitreyi Das, an economics associate at \uc2 HSBC\uc2 , the decision was as straightforward as it can get.\par \par \uc2 "The recent rise in global bond yields \u8212\'20\'14 a rise that has moderated in recent weeks but by no means reversed \u8212\'20\'14 severely limits the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  options," Incalcaterra and Das wrote in a note to clients on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 Also, they noted the rupiah has depreciated since the \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  the last meeting. The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  data showed the currency fell 1 percent against the US dollar since Mar 18.\par \par \uc2 The economists said \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been to make a small intervention in the foreign exchange market to stabilize the currency as foreign portfolio investors pull out their funds when the proceeds from trade surpluses also decline.\par \par \uc2 "With pressure on the rupiah and subdued portfolio inflows, rate cuts are out of the question. BI is instead focusing on banks' progress in reducing lending rates in line with previous \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  rate cuts, and the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  sounded content with the latest progress," Incalcaterra and Das wrote.\par \par \uc2 According to Perry, state-owned lenders, which account for about 40 percent of Indonesia's lending market, have cut their \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  following \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's five interest rate cuts in the past year.\par \par \uc2 The prime lending rate \u8212\'20\'14 the lending rate that lenders charge on the least risky borrowers \u8212\'20\'14 among \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2 , \uc2 Bank Rakyat Indonesia\uc2 , \uc2 Bank Negara Indonesia\uc2 , and \uc2 Bank Tabungan Negara\uc2  have fallen to 8.7 percent on average from 10 percent.\par \par \uc2 On the other hand, only a few private banks have done so. "I invite private banks and the regional development banks (BPD) to lower their basic lending rates immediately," Perry said.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor also said it plans to improve the lending rate transparency in the banking industry "to accelerate monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  transmission to bank lending rates and catalyze lending/financing to the business community."\par \par \uc2 Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  needs all the support it needs from the banks to spur recovery. \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  revised national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth for 2021 outlook to 4.1 to 5.1 percent range, down from its previous projection of 4.5 to 5.5 percent range.\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said that consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which accounts for more than 50 percent of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , remains subdued amid \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  mobility restrictions.\par \par \uc2 Currently, only exports and government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  are driving the growth. As the pace of recovery in developed economies like the United States picks up, the government would also have a harder time attracting buyers to its bonds to finance the government \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs. All of the government bonds issuances have been below target in nearly all auctions since mid-February.\par \par \uc2 HSBC\uc2 's Incalcaterra and Das suggested \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  may urge local banks to channel liquidity into the government bond market, using the Macroprudential Liquidity Buffer instrument.\par \par \uc2 "After all, the banking sector is sitting on a record pool of excess liquidity, a result of the collapse in loan growth. BI may seek to encourage some of those funds to be channeled into the government bond market to facilitate \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  further," Incalcaterra and Das wrote.\par \par \uc2 Document JGLOBE0020210430eh4l00012\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
