\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 INDICATIONS OF  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMIC \highlight\uc2  RECOVERY BECOMING INCREASINGLY APPARENT: PRESIDENTIAL OFFICE\b0\par\par\uc2 574 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 May 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Azis Kurmala\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - The signals of Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery were increasingly visible, particularly from the record trade surplus of US$2.19 billion clocked as of April 2021, according to the Presidential Staff Office (KSP).\par \par \uc2 Deputy III of the Presidential Staff Office Panutan Sulendrakusuma revealed that with trading partners, Indonesia recorded a trade surplus of up to US$1.2 billion with the United States.\par \par \uc2 "The government is optimistic that Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions would continue to experience significant improvements," Sulendrakusuma noted in a written statement in Jakarta, Monday.\par \par \uc2 Apart from a trade surplus with the US, Indonesia also enjoyed a trade surplus of US$554 million with the Philippines, and US$439.9 million with India. However, with several other countries, it experienced a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , such as US$652.1 million with China, US$418.3 million with Australia, and US$248.1 million with Thailand.\par \par \uc2 According to Sulendrakusuma, Indonesia"s trade surplus cannot be separated from the improving export performance. In April 2021, Indonesia"s total exports had reached US$18.48 billion, an increase of 0.69 percent from that recorded in March 2021. Meanwhile, in comparison with April 2020, the total exports in April 2021 increased by 51.94 percent, with details of non-oil and gas exports increasing by 51.08 percent, while oil and gas exports rose by 69.60 percent.\par \par \uc2 Based on commodity groups, non-oil and gas exports in April 2021 reached US$17.52 billion, while oil and gas exports reached US$960 million.\par \par \uc2 "This proves the consistency of the government"s steps to restore the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  amidst the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and dynamics of the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery," Sulendrakusuma stated.\par \par \uc2 The largest increase in non-oil and gas exports in April 2021 against March 2021 was recorded in iron and steel commodities (HS72) amounting to US$246.2 million, an increase of 17.50 percent.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the largest decline was clocked in the animal or vegetable fats and oils (HS15) sector, amounting to US$398.3 million, or a decrease of 13.81 percent.\par \par \uc2 During the January-April 2021 period, exports to China were the largest, valued at US$3.93 billion, followed by US$2.03 billion to the United States, and US$1.32 billion to Japan. The three nations\u8217\'20\'19 exports contributed 41.56 percent to the total export value. Meanwhile, exports to the ASEAN and the \uc2 European Union\uc2  amounted to US$3.59 billion and US$1.39 billion respectively.\par \par \uc2 Sulendrakusuma noted that indications of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery became increasingly apparent from the rise in imports of raw and auxiliary materials and capital goods. In April 2021, the imports of raw and auxiliary materials increased by 33.24 percent, while the imports of capital goods climbed by 11.55 percent as compared to April 2020.\par \par \uc2 "The high increase in imports in the raw and auxiliary materials and capital goods groups shows a sufficient \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery for the second quarter of 2021," he noted.\par \par \uc2 For the record, in April 2021, the total imports were valued at US$16.29 billion. In comparison with April 2020, the total imports increased by 29.93 percent, with details of non-oil and gas imports increasing by 22.10 percent, while oil and gas imports rose by 136.86 percent.\par \par \uc2 EDITED BY INE\par \par \uc2 (T.A063/A/H-SHT/H-SHT) 24-05-2021 14:30:20\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020210524eh5o0008d\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
