\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 INDONESIAN FINANCE MINISTER HIGHLIGHTS PERSISTENT THREAT OF COVID-19\b0\par\par\uc2 349 \uc2 words\par \uc2 31 May 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - The COVID-19 pandemic remains a threat and is causal to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  worldwide, Finance Minister \uc2 Sri Mulyani Indrawati\uc2  stated.\par \par \uc2 "The COVID-19 pandemic continues to pose a threat and creates \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  for any country in the world," Indrawati noted during a plenary meeting of the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  (DPR RI) here on Monday.\par \par \uc2 The minister cited as an example the tsunami of COVID-19 cases in India, although the number of fresh cases had begun to decline at present.\par \par \uc2 Moreover, several countries, including neighboring states, such as Malaysia, the Philippines, and Thailand, were bearing witness to new waves of COVID-19 cases.\par \par \uc2 Indrawati stressed on the need to stringently apply health protocols and ensure fair access to vaccines to tackle the virus.\par \par \uc2 Hence, all countries should work unitedly to end the pandemic, and no one should be left behind in a bid to create a sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery.\par \par \uc2 It would be difficult to achieve \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery if the pandemic is not handled properly, she affirmed.\par \par \uc2 The minister emphasized that the Stage \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  (APBN), as a vital \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  instrument, will always be used for interventions in health management, social protection, and supporting the business world, especially MSMEs.\par \par \uc2 "2020 and 2021 teach us that in the midst of high \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the role of the adaptive, responsive, and flexible APBN is a crucial factor in ensuring that the steps to deal with COVID-19 can be taken," she affirmed.Indrawati stated that the government will continue to make efforts to end the pandemic soon.\par \par \uc2 The 2022 APBN would continue to support structural reform policies to build a new foundation for an inclusive and sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery.\par \par \uc2 "The government really lauds the support and continuous cooperation of all factions in handling the COVID-19 pandemic," she stated.\par \par \uc2 The minister is optimistic that the pandemic would be effectively controlled through various efforts, such as implementing health protocols and increasing testing, tracing, and treatment, as well as vaccination.\par \par \uc2 (T.H-FDH/A/R013/R013) 31-05-2021 13:37:40\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020210531eh5v0005l\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
