\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 APEC\uc2  TRADE MINISTERS' MEETING TO PRIORITIZE VACCINES, ESSENTIAL GOODS\b0\par\par\uc2 500 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 June 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Yuni Arisandy Sinaga\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - The upcoming \uc2 APEC\uc2  Ministers Responsible for Trade (MRT) meeting on June 5 will focus on trade"s vital role in enabling access to vaccines and essential goods and ensuring that the global trading system flows smoothly.\par \par \uc2 New Zealand"s Trade and Export Growth Minister \uc2 Damien O\u8217\'20\'19Connor\uc2  will chair the Virtual APEC Ministers Responsible for Trade (MRT) meeting, according to a release issued by the APEC Secretariat and received here on Thursday.\par \par \uc2 "The Asia-Pacific is confronted by the greatest health and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis of our lifetimes and unprecedented \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as economies continue to struggle to bounce back from COVID-19," Minister O\u8217\'20\'19Connor remarked.\par \par \uc2 The minister noted that these problems demand \uc2 APEC\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s cooperative response.\par \par \uc2 "We know nobody is safe until everybody is safe from COVID-19, and we know that trade has a vital role to ensure our region prospers economically by keeping our markets open to one another rather than closing ourselves off," O"Connor noted.\par \par \uc2 "Responsibility falls on New Zealand, as this year\u8217\'20\'19s host \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to lead an \uc2 APEC\uc2  2021 agenda that responds to these challenges as well as our responsibility for ensuring sustainable recovery," he affirmed.\par \par \uc2 "I will be urging \uc2 APEC\uc2  trade ministers to accelerate access to vaccines and other goods essential in fighting the pandemic by streamlining and speeding up related trade procedures," he emphasized.\par \par \uc2 The APEC Ministers Responsible Trade meeting will focus on two key priorities: trade\u8217\'20\'19s role in responding to COVID-19 and supporting the \uc2 World Trade Organization (WTO) \uc2 that offers predictable trade rules for business.\par \par \uc2 Minister O\u8217\'20\'19Connor drew attention to the worrisome trends of vaccine protectionism and increasingly restricted supply chains affecting the flow of goods and services across the world.\par \par \uc2 The latest report by the APEC \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Support Unit showed that while the average \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  on vaccines is very low within \uc2 APEC\uc2 , at only 0.8 percent, levies are much steeper for several goods that are crucial in the vaccine supply chain.\par \par \uc2 Hence, New Zealand will be seeking cooperation of member economies on ways to eliminate barriers to trade in essential goods and services that are important to sustainable recovery.\par \par \uc2 Ministers will hold discussions on ways to revivify the \uc2 WTO\uc2  to offer consistent and transparent trade rules as well as on what contribution the trade \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  can make to respond to environmental issues, such as climate change and overfishing.\par \par \uc2 A day before the meeting, \uc2 APEC\uc2  trade ministers will also join business leaders to tackle major trade challenges at such a critical time.\par \par \uc2 "The choices we make right now matter. I hope we can look back at this time and know that the \uc2 APEC\uc2  trade ministers took the opportunity to join, work, and grow together to provide vital support for our region\u8217\'20\'19s recovery and to lay the foundations for a better future," Minister O\u8217\'20\'19Connor stated.\par \par \uc2 EDITED BY INE\par \par \uc2 (T.Y012/B/H-SHT/H-SHT) 03-06-2021 18:57:34\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020210603eh6300105\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298