\par\par \b \uc2 The Wrong Time to Increase  \highlight22\uc2 Taxes \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 532 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 June 2021\par \uc2 Tempo.co\par \uc2 TEMPOE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk \par \par \uc2 TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - The government's plan to revise the General \b \highlight22\uc2 Taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  System Law is proposed at the wrong time. the government should cut \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  rather than trying to increase \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenues.\par \par \uc2 The government and the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  (DPR) should not force through the revision to the General \b \highlight22\uc2 Taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  System Law this yeyar. With the current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government must be realistic: this is not the right time to be trying to increase \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenues. If this is forced through, rather tahn recovering, our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could collapse. The plan for the fifth revision to Law No. 6/1983 on general provisions of \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  procedures was sent to the DPR last week. Included in the 2020 National \b \highlight22\uc2 Legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2  Program, all that remains is for the bill to be discussed by the government and the DPR. In the bill, the government wants to apply multi-\b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  value added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and increase personal income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Thi s is all to increase revenues.\par \par \uc2 As well as this, although it is not explicitly stated in the bill, the government has also promised a '\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  amnesty' for those who did not participate in the same program five years ago. This plan was put forward by Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Airlangga Hartarto, who seems to be passing on the aspirations from businesses who have been keen on expreessing this from the outset. There are reports that the finance ministry not very comfortablewith this plan.\par \par \uc2 The lack of unanimity from the the governent over this proram as well as over the procedures for the second \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  amnesty provide more reasons for delaying the deliberations. The bill aimed at improving Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  ration must not turn into vehicle for the interests of a small number of tycoons.\par \par \uc2 It must be admitted that our \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  ratio now is low. In 2020, it was only 8.3 percent of the GDP. This is clearly concerning because countries with strong economies in general have high \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  ratios. However, we should realize that the fall in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  ratio last year was mostly triggered by our worsening \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance. \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth has been negative for the last three quarters - although the trend is now positive. The fall in \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenues led to dramatic reduction in government income. It is predicted that this year will not see a full recovery.\par \par \uc2 Given this fall income, the government should save money by allocating funding only to priority sectors. For example, the plan by the ministry of defense to procure primary weapon systems should be postponed. So should the plan to build a new capital in East Kalimantan. Preisdent Joko Widodo must be at the forefront of efforts to tighten budgetary discipline. He must not be swayed by the idea of increasing growth through large-scale \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . If state funds are used up buying imported goods - such as weapond, submarines and fighter planes - those large \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not affect \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.\par \par \uc2 In the future, \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms should still be a priority. But beforehand, the government must build a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  system trusted by businesspeople and citizens alike.\par \par \uc2 Read the Complete Story in Tempo English Magazine\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://statik.tempo.co/data/0000/00/00/id_/_620.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMPOE0020210605eh65000b5\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
