\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 BI SEES GLOBAL  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMY \highlight\uc2  GROWING 5.8% IN 2021\b0\par\par\uc2 387 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 July 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) \uc2 has projected the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will grow from 5.7 percent to 5.8 percent in 2021 due to increasing financial market \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the spread of the Delta variant of the coronavirus in several countries.\par \par \uc2 One of the factors driving global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery is the revival in international trade, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  said here on Thursday while announcing the results of the July, 2021 board of governors meeting.\par \par \uc2 "Trade volume and world commodity prices are also estimated to be higher, thus supporting improved export performance in developing countries, including Indonesia," he noted.\par \par \uc2 He said BI"s forecast is also supported by an increase in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the United States (US) and the European region, along with the acceleration of vaccinations and continued \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Meanwhile, China"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is also recorded to remain high, he added.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook for India and the ASEAN region is likely to be lower due to the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of restricting people"s mobility to cope with the resurgence of COVID-19 cases, Warjiyo said.\par \par \uc2 However, \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the global financial markets is expected to increase, driven by market concerns about the surge in COVID-19 cases and its impact on the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook, as well as anticipation of plans to reduce monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  or tapering by the US \b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the Fed, he added.\par \par \uc2 These conditions will push the diversion of capital flows to financial assets that are considered safe or flight to quality, resulting in limited capital flows and pressure on exchange rates in developing countries, including Indonesia, he projected.\par \par \uc2 The adjustment of capital outflows from developing countries also caused the rupiah exchange rate on July 21, 2021 to weaken by 0.29 percent point-to-point and 1.14 percent on average compared to at the end of June, 2021, he noted.\par \par \uc2 "With these developments, the rupiah as of July 21, 2021 was recorded to have depreciated around 3.39 percent compared to the figure at the end of 2020, relatively lower than the depreciation of currencies in a number of other developing countries, such as Philippines, Malaysia, and Thailand," Warjiyo said.\par \par \uc2 (T.K012/A/H-SHT/H-SHT) 22-07-2021 23:26:34\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020210722eh7m0028l\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw177\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2655\pichgoal600
