\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 LOW VACCINATION RATES IMPACT  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMIC \highlight\uc2  RECOVERY: MINISTRY\b0\par\par\uc2 461 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 July 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Low vaccination rates in developing countries can potentially impact sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in future, according to the Finance Ministry\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 Fiscal Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Office (BFK).\par \par \uc2 "The pandemic has brought \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We have also learned that expediting vaccination is one of the keys to curbing the number of cases," BFK Head Febrio Kacaribu stated here on Wednesday.\par \par \uc2 Disparities in COVID-19 handling, the speed of vaccination, and the support of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  are causal to uneven \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery.\par \par \uc2 Many developing nations experienced a decline in their \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  projections on account of stricter restrictions being imposed amid the spread of the \uc2 Delta\uc2  variant, Kacaribu pointed out.\par \par \uc2 Several countries whose economies are projected to continue on a downward trajectory were India, at three percent lower than the original forecast; Malaysia, down 1.8 percent from the initial projection; the Philippines, down 1.5 percent; and Thailand, 0.5 percent lower than the initial projection.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the \uc2 IMF\uc2  has projected Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in 2021 to decline by 0.4 percent to 3.9 percent, from the previous 4.3 percent.\par \par \uc2 On the other hand, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  projections of developed nations improved, as they re-opened with high vaccination coverage and massive \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 For instance, the US \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  grew 0.6 percent from the projected figure, the Euro zone was up 0.2 percent from the initial projection, and South Korea\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  advanced 0.7 percent from the original projection.\par \par \uc2 He noted that at the global level, especially world leaders at the G20 forum had channeled all their resources to overcome the new wave of COVID-19 due to the \uc2 Delta\uc2  variant.\par \par \uc2 Leaders of developed countries ensured equal vaccine distribution among their people. They also secured funds to provide \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  to the health sector and for social protection, according to Kacaribu.\par \par \uc2 "Indonesia has targeted to push its daily vaccination numbers to 1.5 million doses. We will gradually increase the number," he noted.\par \par \uc2 As of July 27, the Indonesian government had sent out 63.94 million vaccine doses to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The government has ensured the availability of vaccine stocks to expedite vaccination. The government had also extended the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity restrictions (PPKM) level 4 until August 2 in a bid to better handle the pandemic, and as a consequence, the daily count of cases had continued to decline.\par \par \uc2 He believes that by tightening policies and going the extra mile in the health sector, Indonesia can tackle the pandemic in order to facilitate \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery.\par \par \uc2 "We are also streamlining our state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to provide more social aid and support for SMEs accompanied by efforts to accelerate the distribution," he said.\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-RST/A/H-FDH/H-FDH) 28-07-2021 18:40:20\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA002021072