\par\par \b \uc2 Crypto investing now more popular than stock market\b0\par\par\uc2 Eisya A. Eloksari, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 736 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 August 2021\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 2\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2021 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Crypto assets have rapidly gained in popularity among Indonesians despite -- or perhaps because of -- theglobal \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown.\par \par \uc2 According to the Trade Ministry, crypto investment transactions grew fivefold in fivemonths to more than Rp 370 trillion (US$25.8 billion) in May.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia had around 6.5 million crypto investors in May, while the number of retail investors registered with the \uc2 Indonesia Stock Exchange\uc2  (IDX) stood at just 5.37 million.\par \par \uc2 "Some crypto assets have showna positive performance amid the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  downturn due to the pandemic. Investors and traders will switch to more attractive ways to boost their gains, one of which is crypto assets. Therefore, we have seen exponential growth since the third quarter of 2020," Rieka Handayani, head of PR at cryptocurrency exchange platform Tokocrypto, told The Jakarta Post on Wednesday.\par \par \uc2 Tokocrypto is backed by one of the leading global cryptocurrency exchanges, Binance.\par \par \uc2 Rieka went on to say that Tokocrypto had more than 90,000 weekly active traders in the first quarter of the year, with a daily average trading volume of around US$40 million to $70 million.\par \par \uc2 Stephen DeMeulenaere, lead adviser at IDK Foundation, which issues IDK cryptocurrency tokens, explained thatas more people in Indonesia gotinternet access, digital currencies would become increasingly mainstream.\par \par \uc2 "We believe blockchain-based digital currencies and financial services are primed for significant growth as this technology matures and becomes easier to use," he said in an email interview on Wednesday.\par \par \uc2 A so-called stablecoin, IDK pegs its value to the Indonesian rupiah with the purpose of creating a fiat-linked blockchain asset that can be bought and sold for other cryptocurrencies.\par \par \uc2 DeMeulenaere said IDK was predominantly used by crypto traders to settle transactions.\par \par \uc2 Unlike other cryptocurrencies, which can fluctuate dramatically in value against the US dollar or other currencies, stablecoins do not change significantly in value against the fiat currency they are linked to. For this reason, some stablecoins are popular for cross-border transfers and remittances.\par \par \uc2 "This is because transferring fiat currency in and out of the traditional banking system takes more time," DeMeulenaere explained, adding, however, that IDK Foundation had "not seen significant activities in this area yet".\par \par \uc2 Rieka and DeMeulenaere agreed that the popularity of cryptocurrencies had beenheavily influenced by information on social media and the level of trust vested in the asset class around the world.\par \par \uc2 The rising popularity of crypto assets has prompted the Trade Ministry's Futures Exchange Supervisory Board (Bappebti) to establish a more protected trading environment.\par \par \uc2 "Bappebti is verifying the required documents for a crypto assetexchange," Bappebti market development head Suhadi said on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 Bappebti head Indrasari Wisnu Wardhana said in June that the government would set up a clearing and depository institution to ensure the safety of investors'funds. The clearinghouse would keep 70 percent of exchanges' assets as default funds and retain the ability to freeze funds ifdefaults occurred.\par \par \uc2 "The crypto asset exchange will play a big role in ensuring the safety of the crypto ecosystem in Indonesia. There will be checks and balances [...], increased market conducivenessas well as increasing certainty and legality," Rieka of Tokocrypto said.\par \par \uc2 Bappebti has been tightening regulations over cryptocurrency trading. It issued licenses for 13 cryptocurrency trading platforms in February as well as a \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  that recognized 229 cryptocurrencies as legally tradable commodities in December.\par \par \uc2 Crypto marketplaces are subject to corporate income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  (PPh Badan), and the government is in the process of preparing a type of final income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  (PPh Final) to be imposed on virtual currency transactions.\par \par \uc2 Institute for Development of Economics and Finance (Indef) economist Eko Listiyanto said \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue was the most viable way for crypto trading to contribute to Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , while there was no obvious benefit for the real sector.\par \par \uc2 "Beside \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  [...], the benefits of crypto assets for the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  are \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 . If the price of bitcoin keeps rising, investors' money will go there and not to the real sector," he told the Post in a phone interview on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 Eko said investors were opting for crypto assets because bank deposits and the stock market were less attractive amid the pandemic-induced global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown.\par \par \uc2 "If the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery can be accelerated, I think people will go back to investing in the stock market or other commodities because of better fundamentals, and some cryptocurrencies will not survive this," he added.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020210805eh850005z\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
