\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 PRESIDENT TARGETS  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMIC \highlight\uc2  GROWTH OF 5-5.5 PERCENT BY 2022\b0\par\par\uc2 458 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 August 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - President \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2  (Jokowi) is eyeing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of around 5-5.5 percent by 2022, though the government will strive to reach the upper bracket of this band.\par \par \uc2 "\b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in 2022 is estimated to lie around five percent to 5.5 percent. We will try our best to achieve the upper limit of the growth target at 5.5 percent," President Jokowi noted in a speech on the Bill of the State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  (APBN) for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  Year 2022 and Financial Notes before the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19 plenary session for the 2021-2022 Session Year at the parliament complex here on Monday.\par \par \uc2 The head of state noted that the estimated \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target took into account the highly dynamic developments pertaining to the COVID-19 pandemic.\par \par \uc2 President Jokowi stressed that the government will mobilize all resources, scientific analysis, and expert views to tackle the COVID-19 pandemic in Indonesia in a bid to maintain, expedite, and bolster \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery and social welfare.\par \par \uc2 The president remarked that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth rate also mirrored the projected strong \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, supported by investment and export growth as a result of the implementation of structural reforms. However, the government should nonetheless stay alert on account of global and domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  that can affect \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in future.\par \par \uc2 "Inflation will be maintained at three percent, reflecting an increase in demand, both due to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery and improvement in the people"s purchasing power," according to President Jokowi.\par \par \uc2 In addition, the rupiah is estimated to strengthen by around Rp14,350 per US dollar and the interest rate on 10-year government bonds is estimated to reach around 6.82 percent, reflecting Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals and the influence of global dynamics.\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, the price of Indonesian crude oil (ICP) is expected to reach around US$63 per barrel. Oil and gas lifting is estimated at 703,000 barrels and 1,036,000 barrels of oil equivalent per day, respectively.\par \par \uc2 President Jokowi noted that the government had adopted the theme "\b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Recovery and Structural Reform" in the 2022 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The head of state believes that social and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery will continue to improve to strengthen the foundation and support structural reforms more optimally.\par \par \uc2 "Structural reforms are very fundamental for the recovery and acceleration of post-pandemic \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth since Indonesia must grow quickly and sustainably," according to the president.\par \par \uc2 Hence, productivity must be increased by improving the quality of human resources, supported by more equitable connectivity, and accelerating infrastructure development, including digital, energy and food infrastructure, to encourage industrialization as well as ecosystem support, Jokowi noted.\par \par \uc2 (T.K012/A/S022/S022) 16-08-2021 19:20:32\par \par \uc2 Document AN