\par\par \uc2 NATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 HOUSEHOLD CONSUMPTION SEEN CONTRIBUTING 54% TO  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMY \highlight\uc2  IN 2022\b0\par\par\uc2 394 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 August 2021\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - The contribution of household consumption to Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is expected to rise up to 54 percent in 2022, reflecting a normal level of growth of 5 to 5.3 percent,according to the second financial note of the 2022 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft bill.\par \par \uc2 In comparison, 2.2-2.8 percent growth in household consumption has been projected for the second half of 2021.\par \par \uc2 "The growth of household consumption in 2022 will be attributed to better \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity and mobility patterns after recovering from COVID-19 pandemic escalation be it in 2020 or 2021," according to the draft bill accessed from Jakarta on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 Successful controlling of the pandemic will boost \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  confidence in performing activities as they normally did prior to the pandemic, it stated.\par \par \uc2 In addition, government \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  support for strengthening social protection programs for the poor will also be an important factor in encouraging or pushing \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  consumption.\par \par \uc2 Reinforcement of social protection programs will be carried out by integrating data, improving distribution mechanisms, and synergizing relevant programs, including \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs for the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Stable inflation in the range of 3 \u177\'00\'B1 1 percent on a continuous basis will also help to maintain people"s ability to buy things.\par \par \uc2 The momentum of strong and just \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in the first half of 2021 needs to be maintained, although anticipation must be practiced due to high \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  from the spike in COVID-19 cases, according to the note.\par \par \uc2 Since mid-June 2021, there has been a spike in COVID-19 cases in Indonesia due to the emergence of the Delta variant, which spreads very quickly.\par \par \uc2 The government has responded quickly to the surge by enforcing Level 4 community activity restrictions (PPKM) in various regions, prioritizing COVID-19 handling to ensure that citizens stay safe and healthy.\par \par \uc2 In addition to that \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government has also continued to conduct mass vaccination programs, which aim to reach more people by the end of the year.\par \par \uc2 Earlier, President \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2  had said that he hoped to see 70 percent of Indonesians vaccinated by December 2021.\par \par \uc2 The effectiveness of the pandemic control \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will be the key to the sustainability of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in the second half of 2021, he added.\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-MCA/A/R013/R013) 17-08-2021 18:41:52\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020210817eh8h001jl\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
